    <ui:define name="content">

        <h2>Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
            Job Finder is a web-based job tracking system developed as part of the CS5003 coursework project.
            The platform allows users to browse available job opportunities, track jobs,
            and manage tracked jobs.
        </p>

        <h2>What You Can Do</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Register and log in securely</li>
            <li>Browse available jobs</li>
            <li>Search using AJAX-powered filtering</li>
            <li>Track jobs you are interested in</li>
            <li>Create, edit and delete job listings</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Technology Used</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Jakarta Server Faces (JSF)</li>
            <li>Jakarta Persistence API (JPA)</li>
            <li>GlassFish Server</li>
            <li>Apache Derby (JavaDB)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            This project was developed as a group coursework submission for CS5003.
        </p>

    </ui:define>

</ui:composition>
